INVESTIGATION OF,@80-96@ CIA DENIES SLAIN BARRY SEAL WORKED FOR THE IT~ BUT HE WAS AN INFORMANT FOR DEA A NEWLY RELEASED CIA DOCUMENT IN WHICH IT ADMITS TIES TO THE INTER MOUNTAIN REGIONAL AIRPORT~ NEAR MENA~ ARK.~ FROM WHICH SEAL OPERATED. CIA SAID IT ONLY CONTRACTED OUT ^FOR ROUTINE AVIATION SERVICES.^ PAPERS RELEASED FRIDAY AND REFERRED TO BY THE CIA AS ^AN UNCLASSIFIED SUMMARY~^ SAID BARRY SEAL BECAME AN INFORMANT FOR THE DEA AFTER BEING ARRESTED FOR SMUGGLING COCAINE. HE SAID HE COULD PROVIDE PROOF THAT SANDANISTAS WERE RUNNING DRUGS TO THE UNITED STATES. HE HAD BEEN FLYING OUT OF MENA~ PICKING UP DRUGS~ AND RETURNING TO DROP POINTS IN TEXAS~ LOUISIANA AND ARKANSAS~ WHERE A GROUND CREW COLLECTED THE CONTRABAND~ PER RETIRED ARKANSAS STATE POLICE INVESTIGATOR RUSSELL WELCH. HIS PLANE -- A C-123 MILITARY TRANSPORT -- HAD SOPHISTICATED SURVEILLANCE CAMERAS. SEAL RETURNED TO THE U.S. FROM ONE TRIP WITH A LOAD OF DRUGS AND CLAIMS HE HAD PHOTOS OF A TOP SANDANISTA OFFICIAL AND UNIFORMED SANDANISTA SOLDIERS LOADING DRUGS ONTO THE AIRPLANE. SEAL WAS DESCRIBED IN A HEAVILY CENSURED DOCUMENT CALLED A ^SUMMARY OF CONTRA PARTICIPANTS~ CONFIDENTIAL WITNESS LIST~^ OBTAINED FROM FBI UNDER FOIA AS HAVING ^HAD DEEP AND UNKNOWN TIES^ WITH CIA OFFICIALS. THE C-123 REGISTERED TO SEAL WAS USED IN THE DEA-CIA SANDANISTA STING WAS SHOT DOWN SEVEN MONTHS LATER OVER NICARAGUA WHILE FLYING SUPPLIES TO THE ANTI-COMMUNIST CONTRAS. UPI 11/11/96
