INVESTIGATION OF,@94-96 ALL OF POST AMES REVIEWS: COUNCIL ON FOREIGN RELATIONS' STUDY~ ^MAKING INTEL SMARTER;^ COMMISSION ON ROLES AND CAPABILITIES OF THE U.S. INTEL COMMUNITY'S STUDY: ^PREPARING FOR THE 21ST CENTURY;^ 1994-1995 STUDY BY INSTITUTE FOR THE STUDY OF DIPLOMACY AT GEORGETOWN ON ^AMERICAN INTEL FOR THE TWENTY-FIRST CENTURY^ -- ALL OPT FOR A STRONGER CIA LED BY A DIRECTOR OF CENTRAL INTEL WHO HAS REAL AUTHORITY OVER ENTIRE INTEL COMMUNITY (IC). (THIS RECOMMENDATION HAS BEEN AROUND SINCE AT LEAST EISENHOWER PRESIDENCY). NOT SURPRISINGLY PARTICIPANTS IN ALL ^STUDIES^ CAME FROM HARD-LINERS MANY OF WHOM ARE VETERANS OF THE IC. NONE APPARENTLY DREW GUIDANCE FROM REPUTABLE DISSIDENTS. MANY PARTICIPANTS WERE INVOLVED IN MORE THAN ONE STUDY AND STUDIES ALL REACH SAME CONCLUSION -- GIVE MORE POWER TO CIA. STUDIES FOCUS ON INTEL CAPABILITIES. THIS STRESSED OVER AND OVER AGAIN. ORWELLIAN NEWSPEAK OF STUDIES HIDES REAL PURPOSE OF CIA -- COVERT OPS. ALL OF THESE EXERCISES IN PUBLIC RELATIONS WERE GENERATED TO ^ALLOW FOR A COOLING OFF PERIOD~^ NOT TO AFFECT CHANGE. CIABASE 3/96
INVESTIGATION OF,@94-96@ A. COMMISSION ON ROLES AND CAPABILITIES OF U.S. INTEL COMMITTEE REPORT. U.S. INTEL [BEST IN WORLD]. BUT MORE MONEY NEEDED. BY AUTUMN OF 94 PROBLEMS TOOK THEIR TOLL ON CREDIBILITY OF INTEL. SUMMARY: COMMISSION CHARTERED BY CONGRESS IN 10/94 AND BEGAN OPS IN 3/95. TESTIMONY FROM 84 WITNESSES~ AND STAFF INTERVIEWED 200 OTHERS. U.S. NEEDS TO MAINTAIN STRONG INTEL CAPABILITY. PERFORMANCE CAN BE IMPROVED. INTEL NEEDS TO BE CLOSER TO [POLICYMAKERS]. MUST FUNCTION MORE CLOSELY AS A COMMUNITY. SHOULD OPERATE MORE EFFICIENTLY. CONFIDENCE MOST BE RESTORED. SUPPORT TO U.S. DIPLOMACY~ MILITARY OPS AND DEFENSE PLANNING SHOULD BE PRINCIPLE MISSION. IT SHOULD NOT BECOME INVOLVED IN INDUSTRIAL ESPIONAGE. IT SHOULD REPORT ON UNFAIR TRADE PRACTICES. CIA HAS HAD IMPORTANT SUCCESS. IMPROVE ANALYSTS AND ANALYSIS AND MAKE MORE USE OF OPEN SOURCES AND OUTSIDE EXPERTS. NEED TO RIGHTSIZE - I.E. DOWNSIZE SOME INTEL AGENCIES. DOD HUMINT SHOULD BE RESPONSIBILITY OF ONLY THE CIA NOT THE DOD. BUT ACTIVE DUTY MILITARY OFFICERS WITH DOD HUMINT SERVICE SHOULD BE TRANSFERRED TO CIA. CHAPTER 1 PRAISES CIA AND ITS INTELLIGENCE AND ARGUES TO PRESERVE IT. (13). IT ADVISES THAT INTEL SERVICES NOT COLLECT OPEN INFO. (16). IT ARGUES FOR CONTINUING COVERT ACTION. (18). RESPONSIBILITY FOR PARAMILITARY COVERT OPS SHOULD REMAIN WITH CIA. (19). COUNTERINTEL MUST BE SUSTAINED. (20). ECONOMIC INTEL SHOULD NOT GIVE PROPRIETARY INFO TO CORPORATIONS BUT SHOULD PROVIDE INFO ON UNFAIR TRADE PRACTICES. CIA SHOULD CONTINUE ANTIDRUG OPS. ROLES REPORT. 3/95
INVESTIGATION OF,@94@ ARLINGTON~ VA~ 12/3/94 ROBERT STEELE~ OPEN SOURCES SOLUTIONS~ CALLED FOR IMMEDIATE ELIMINATION OF CIA. CIA IS IN FINAL STAGES~ OF BUREAUCRATIC CANCER. ARTICLE 11/94 ISSUE OF STEELE'S ORG'S NEWSLETTER~ ^OSS NOTICES^ CALLED FOR ELIMINATION OF CIA WHILE CALLING FOR FOUR NEW INITIATIVES: A SEPARATE CLANDESTINE SERVICES AGENCY; A MORE POWERFUL NATIONAL INTEL COUNCIL TO BE MOVED CLOSER TO ITS CUSTOMERS; AN INTER-AGENCY INTEL ANALYSIS CONSORTIUM; AND A NATIONAL INFO FOUNDATION. TO NURTURE DISTRIBUTED CENTERS OF EXCELLENCE IN THE PRIVATE SECTOR. STEELE SAID CIA IS HAVING AN IDENTITY CRISIS IN LARGE PART BECAUSE IT IS FOUR COMPLETELY SEPARATE FIEFDOMS THAT DO NOT TALK TO EACH OTHER AND ARE NOT BY ANY STRETCH OF THE IMAGINATION RESPONSIVE TO DIRECTION FROM DCI. CIA COMBINES A BLOATED ADM STRUCTURE WITH A HALF-WAY HOUSE FOR TECHNICAL RESEARCH ADDICTS~ AND THEN ADDS BUTTON-DOWN SCHOOL BOYS TRYING TO BE SPIES FROM WITHIN OFFICIAL INSTALLATIONS WHERE THEY ARE EASY TO SPOT~ AND TOPS THIS OFF WITH A WHOLE BUNCH OF ANALYSTS THAT DON'T SPEAK A FOREIGN LANGUAGE~ HAVE RARELY BEEN OVERSEAS~ AND HAVE ALMOST NO ACCESS TO PRIVATE SECTOR EXPERTS IN THEIR TOPICAL AREAS. WE DESPERATELY NEED A NEW AND LARGER CLANDESTINE CAPABILITY~ ONE WHICH IS NOT A LAUGHINGSTOCK WORLD-WIDE. THERE ISN'T A SINGLE COUNTRY OUT THERE WHERE THE LOCAL AUTHORITIES ARE NOT FULLY AWARE OF WHO CIA OFFICERS ARE~ AND WHO THEIR AGENTS ARE. IN CLOSE CONSULTATION WITH WHITE HOUSE AND ASPIN COMMISSION~ WE [SHOULD OPT] FOR A COMPLETELY NON-OFFICIAL COVER SERVICES AGENCY~ AND FOR PHASING OUT THE EXISTING AND EASILY IDENTIFIED OFFICIAL COVER CAPABILITIES. OSS NOTICES 11/94
