INVESTIGATION OF,@95@ ASPIN COMMISSION GETS DOWN TO WORK ON OPEN SOURCES. ON 3 AUGUST 1995 NATIONAL SECURITY ADVISOR ANTHONY LAKE WILL BE THE FIRST WITNESS IN TESTIMONY TO THE ASSEMBLED COMMISSIONERS OF THE ASPIN COMMISSION WHICH IS STUDYING THE ROLES AND MISSIONS OF THE U.S. INTELLIGENCE COMMUNITY. HE WILL BE FOLLOWED IN TESTIMONY BY ROBERT D. STEELE~ HEAD OF OPEN SOURCE SOLUTIONS~ INC.~ WHO HAS BEEN ASKED TO COMMENT ON HOW OPEN SOURCES CAN HELP THE INTELLIGENCE COMMUNITY ACHIEVE SAVINGS~ SATISFY MORE CONSUMERS~ AND REDIRECT ITS CLANDESTINE AND TECHNICAL CAPABILITIES. MR. STEELE~ AND THEREFORE OPEN SOURCE INTELLIGENCE~ APPEAR TO HAVE FINALLY ACHIEVED MAINSTREAM STATUS IN THE U.S. IN RECENT MONTHS~ STEELE HAS BEEN THE FEATURED SPEAKER AT A TOP SECRET CONFERENCE ON THE FUTURE OF U.S. INTEL HELD AT NSA. STEELE~ A FORMER CIA CASE OFFICER WITH THREE OVERSEAS TOURS AND MANY AGENT RECRUITMENTS TO HIS CREDIT~ IS UNUSUAL FOR HAVING ALSO ACQUIRED EXPERIENCE IN IMAGERY AND SIGNALS INTEL~ AS WELL AS ANALYSIS. HE WAS THE SENIOR CIVILIAN RESPONSIBLE FOR SETTING UP THE MARINE CORPS INTEL CENTER~ AND SERVED AS THE STUDY DIRECTOR FOR THAT CENTER'S FIRST MAJOR ANALYSIS SERIES. <INT 7/24/95 35
