INVESTIGATION OF,@95@ ON 6/5/95 THE ASPIN COMMISSION PRODUCED A REPORT~ ^SCOPE OF THE COMMISSION'S INQUIRY~^ OUTLINING THE PANEL'S WORK PLAN FOR REFORMING U.S. INTEL AND PRESENTED FOUR KEY RESPONSIBILITIES: IDENTIFYING U.S. INTEL NEEDS AND PRIORITIES; EXAMINING THE CURRENT ORGANIZATIONAL STRUCTURE TO DEVELOP THE MOST EFFICIENT FRAMEWORK POSSIBLE; DETERMINING IF THE CURRENT INTELLIGENCE BUDGET IS JUSTIFIED AND ADEQUATE; AND EXPLORING OTHER INTELLIGENCE ISSUES TO IMPROVE EFFECTIVENESS AND EFFICIENCY. FOLLOWING THE DEATH IN APRIL OF CHAIRMAN LES ASPIN~ PRESIDENT CLINTON APPOINTED HAROLD BROWN~ PRESIDENT JIMMY CARTER'S DEFENSE SECRETARY AND CURRENTLY COUNSELOR AT THE CENTER FOR STRATEGIC AND INTERNATIONAL STUDIES IN WASHINGTON. <INT 7/24/95 35
INVESTIGATION OF,@95@ REORGANIZING INTELLIGENCE OR LETTING IT DRIFT? SOURCES CLOSE TO THE ADM REPORT GREAT CONFUSION BOTH WITHIN SENIOR STAFF UNDER DCI AND THE FEW KEY PERSONNEL ON THE NSC WITH NOMINAL RESPONSIBILITIES FOR INTELLIGENCE. TENDENCY OF THE ADM IS TO LET INTELLIGENCE REORGANIZATION DRIFT WHILE AWAITING RESULTS OF THE ASPIN COMMISSION. THIS TACTIC PLEASES ENTRENCHED INTELLIGENCE COMMUNITY BUREAUCRATS FOR WHOM ANOTHER YEAR OF STATUS QUO IS ANOTHER YEAR IN POWER. OFFICIALS CLOSE TO ASPIN COMMISSION AND KEY CONGRESSIONAL STAFF MEMBERS ARE RALLYING TO THE CALL OF ^PREPARE FOR THE FUTURE - NO DRIFTING ALLOWED.^ KEY PLAYERS IN CONGRESS SEEM TO SHOW MORE PROMISE [THAN NSC] AND IT IS ON THE HILL THAT MOST OBSERVERS EXPECT PROGRESS TO BE MADE. KEY STAFFERS INCLUDE CHRIS STRAUB~ MINORITY STAFF DIRECTOR ON SENATE SELECT COMMITTEE FOR INTELLIGENCE~ THE PERSONAL APPOINTEE OF SENIOR DEMOCRAT BOB KERREY~ WHO~ UNTIL REPUBLICAN LANDSLIDE~ FULLY EXPECTED TO BE CHAIRMAN. AT THE HOUSE~ NEW STAFF DIRECTOR DR. MARK LOWENTHAL~ A WIDELY-PUBLISHED AND HIGHLY DISTINGUISHED PROFESSIONAL~ IS EXPECTED TO SUPPORT COMMITTEE MEMBERS WITH INNOVATIVE AND FAR-REACHING PROPOSALS FOR CHANGE. INTELLIGENCE 1/16/95 256/25
