INVESTIGATION OF,CUBA~ @61-62@ TAYLOR COMMITTEE INVESTIGATED FAILURE OF THE BAY OF PIGS OP. SCHLESINGER CONCLUDED: COMMITTEE'S REAL FUNCTION WAS TO PRESERVE CIA AND JCS FROM FEELINGS OF PROSECUTION. COMMITTEE CONCLUDED OP WAS INADEQUATE AND JCS SERVED PRESIDENT POORLY. CIA SHARED THE BLAME. TAYLOR COMMITTEE CONCLUDED CIA WAS POORLY SUITED FOR LARGE-SCALE PARAMILITARY OPS AND THAT FUTURE SUCH OPS BE CARRIED OUT BY PENTAGON. IN 6/61~ KENNEDY SIGNED NATIONAL SECURITY ACTION MEMORANDUM 55 AND 57~ WHICH TRANSFERRED LARGE-SCALE PM OPS FROM CIA TO DOD AND GAVE JCS CHAIRMAN FULL RESPONSIBILITY FOR THESE OPS. <NAS 184-6
INVESTIGATION OF,CUBA~ @61@ FOLLOWING BAY OF PIGS DISASTER KENNEDY ORDERED FULL-SCALE SHAKE UP OF CIA INCLUDING INTERNAL INVESTIGATION BY INSPECTOR GENERAL LYMAN KIRKPATRICK. KIRKPATRICK'S REPORT WAS A RUTHLESS ATTACK ON DULLES AND BISSELL. <SFA 364
INVESTIGATION OF,CUBA~ @61@ IN JUN 61~ CUBAN STUDY GROUP (TAYLOR COMMISSION) CONCLUDED THAT A PARAMILITARY OPERATION SIZE OF BAY OF PIGS COULD NOT BE PREPARED AND CONDUCTED IN SUCH A WAY THAT ALL U.S. SUPPORT OF IT AND CONNECTION WITH IT COULD BE PLAUSIBLY DISCLAIMED. ALSO NOTED PRES AND SENIOR OFFICIALS WERE GREATLY INFLUENCED BY UNDERSTANDING THAT LANDING FORCE COULD PASS TO GUERRILLA STATUS. OFFICIALS ALSO FELT CUBAN BRIGADE WAS A WANING ASSET AND HAD TO BE USED QUICKLY - FEARED DISPOSING BRIGADE WOULD BE PROBLEMATIC IF OPERATION WAS SCRUBBED. <OZ 40~41
INVESTIGATION OF,CUBA~ @61@ INSPECTOR GENERAL LYMAN KIRKPATRICK PRODUCED ^A VERY SEVERE REPORT^ RE BAY OF PIGS OP. DCI MCCONE ORDERED ALL COPIES OF REPORT DESTROYED AND KEPT ORIGINAL IN HIS PRIVATE FILES. <WOM 120
