INVESTIGATION OF,GUATEMALA~ @90-95@ CLINTON ADM TO SECURE DOCUMENTS RE U.S. GVT ROLE IN TWO DEATHS ALEGEDLY ORDERED BY A GUATEMALAN COLONEL~ WHO WAS A CIA INFORMER. IOB TO INVESTIGATE. TWO KILLED WERE MICHAEL DEVINE~ THE OTHER WAS A GUERRILLA FIGHTER~ EFRAIM BAMACA VELASQUEZ. REPRESENTATIVE TORRICELLI DISCLOSED COL. JULIO ROBERTO ALPIREZ THE MAN RESPONSIBLE WAS PAID $44~000 BY CIA IN 92. UNSIGNED LETTER RECEIVED BY TORRICELLI PRINTED ON NSA STATIONERY~ CLAIMED EXTENSIVE COMMUNICATIONS INTERCEPTS CLEARLY SUBSTANTIATE CIA AND DOD KNEW~ AT THE TIME~ CIRCUMSTANCES OF MURDERS. U.S. SPECIAL FORCES PERSONNEL WERE GIVING COLONEL ALPIREZ INFO RE BAMACA AND MICHAEL DEVINE - THAT MAY HAVE LEAD TO THEIR DEATHS. LETTER CLAIMED COL DANIEL DAY AN ARMY INTEL OFFICER ASSIGNED TO NSA~ WAS WORKING WITH ARMY DEPUTY CHIEF OF STAFF FOR INTEL TO PURGE COMMINCATIONS INTERCEPTS. <WP 3/30/95 A1~10
