INVESTIGATION OF,HONDURAS~ @93-97@ CIA SAID AN INTERNAL INVESTIGATION FOUND NO EVIDENCE ITS AGENTS WERE INVOLVED IN THE DISAPPEARANCE OF A U.S. JESUIT PRIEST IN HONDURAS IN 1983. CIA ALSO SAID IT HAS FAILED TO REACH ANY CONCLUSION ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED TO JAMES FRANCIS CARNEY. CARNEY DISAPPEARED IN AUGUST OR SEPTEMBER 1983~ IN A LEFTIST INCURSION INTO HONDURAS FROM NICARAGUA. IN HIS BOOK~ ``AN AMERICAN PRIEST IN HONDURAS~'' CARNEY ADMITTED BEING A MEMBER OF THE POPULAR ARMED FORCES~ THE MILITARY ARM OF THE REVOLUTIONARY WORKERS PARTY. THIRTY-SIX DOCUMENTS REVIEWED BY CIA COVERING 14 YEARS OF SPORADIC REPORTING ON THE PRIEST~ RELEASED BY THE CIA~ SUGGEST THREE POSSIBLE SCENARIOS FOR CARNEY'S DISAPPEARANCE. ^... WE FOUND NO INFO TO INDICATE CIA WAS INVOLVED...^ AP 3/12/97
