ITALY,ITALY~ @95@ A FORMER CIA AGENT WAS ARRESTED IN CONNECTION WITH A PROBE INTO A MONEY LAUNDERING RING THAT HAS INVOLVED THE ROMAN CATHOLIC ARCHBISHOP OF BARCELONA. ROGER D'ONOFRIO~ A 72-YEAR-OLD RETIRED AGENT OF CIA~ WITH DUAL U.S.-ITALIAN CITIZENSHIP~ WAS ARRESTED AT HIS HOME NEAR NAPLES. PROSECUTORS IN OP ^CHEQUE TO CHEQUE^ SUSPECT THAT D'ONOFRIO USED HIS CIA CONTACTS TO HELP AN INTERNATIONAL RING LAUNDER MONEY AND TRAFFICK IN ARMS~ DRUGS AND RADIOACTIVE MATERIALS. THE PROSECUTOR ORMANNI SPARKED AN UPROAR WHEN HE ASKED SPAIN FOR PERMISSION TO QUESTION CARDINAL RICARD MARIA CARLES~ THE ARCHBISHOP OF BARCELONA. REPORTS IN ITALIAN AND SPANISH NEWSPAPERS ALLEGE THAT CARLES OVERSAW THE LAUNDERING OF SOME $65 MILLION IN LIRE INTO DOLLARS THROUGH THE VATICAN BANK~ THE INSTITUTE OF RELIGIOUS WORK (IOR). CARLES HAS DENIED ANY WRONGDOING~ WHILE THE VATICAN JUMPED TO HIS DEFENSE AND DENIED THE REPORTS. BARCELONA POLICE HAVE SAID THEY FOUND THERE WAS NOT ^THE SLIGHTEST PROOF^ THAT CARLES WAS IMPLICATED. REUTER 12/2/95
