KGB,USSR~ @50-99 SOVIET KGB MOUNTED A MASSIVE BUGGING OP IN THE 1970S AND EARLY '80S THAT PROVIDED INTEL ON EVERYTHING FROM KISSINGER'S PHONE CONVERSATIONS TO TOP-SECRET WEAPONS~ PER A SOVIET DEFECTOR. EXPERTS SAID USSR EXCELLED IN THE FIELD OF HUMAN INTEL~ DEMONSTRATED BY ITS ABILITY TO RECRUIT HUNDREDS OF INFORMERS IN THE U.S FOR EITHER IDEOLOGICAL OR MERCENARY MOTIVES. A BOOK DRAWING ON NOTES SMUGGLED OUT BY A FORMER KGB ARCHIVIST ASSERTS THAT USSR MISSIONS IN WASHINGTON AND NEW YORK WERE THE HUB OF AN EAVESDROPPING OP. ONE KGB DOCUMENT CITED BY THE DEFECTOR~ VASILI MITROKHIN~ CLAIMED THAT MORE THAN HALF THE PROJECTS OF THE SOVIET DEFENSE INDUSTRY IN 1979 WERE BASED ON INTEL FROM THE WEST. MITROKHIN~ WHO DEFECTED TO BRITAIN IN 1992 AFTER BEING TURNED AWAY BY CIA~ TOOK NOTES ON SOME OF THE KGB'S FILES OVER A 12-YEAR PERIOD PRIOR TO HIS RETIREMENT IN 1984. HE SMUGGLED THE NOTES OUT IN HIS SHOES AND POCKETS~ AND BURIED THEM UNDER THE FLOORBOARDS OF HIS DACHA~ OR COUNTRY HOME. ^THE SWORD AND THE SHIELD^ BY MITROKHIN AND HIS BRITISH CO-AUTHOR~ CHRISTOPHER ANDREW~ INCLUDES: THE KGB SOUGHT TO LINK THE CIA TO THE ASSASSINATION OF PRESIDENT KENNEDY BY FORGING A LETTER FROM LEE HARVEY OSWALD TO A CIA OFFICER~ E. HOWARD HUNT. THE LETTER~ WHICH INDICATED THAT OSWALD WANTED TO MEET HUNT BEFORE GOING AHEAD WITH THE KILLING~ WAS FABRICATED IN THE MID-'70S AFTER HUNT'S NAME APPEARED IN THE PRESS IN CONNECTION WITH THE WATERGATE SCANDAL. KGB PLANNED TO SABOTAGE THE FLATHEAD DAM IN MONTANA~ THE PORT OF NEW YORK~ AND POWER SUPPLIES OF NEW YORK STATE. A BOOBY-TRAPPED ARMS CACHE WAS RECENTLY DISCOVERED AND DESTROYED IN SWITZERLAND~ AND THE AUTHORS BELIEVE SIMILAR ARMS CACHES COULD BE SCATTERED ACROSS THE UNITED STATES. <WP 9/14/99 A2
