KGB,USSR~ @80-89@ KGB AIMED TO INFILTRATE AND ESTABLISH A PRESENCE IN THE VATICAN IN THE 1980S. KGB IN ROME ATTEMPTED TO GAIN INTEL ON VATICAN OBJECTIVES~ PARTICULARLY IN LIGHT OF THE WEST'S USE OF THE CATHOLIC CHURCH AT THE TIME IN CULTIVATING ANTI-SOVIET~ ANTI-SOCIALIST SENTIMENT. THE KGB WAS NOT LOOKING FOR DIRECT CONTACTS WITHIN THE VATICAN~ BUT SIMPLY LOW-LEVEL~ POORLY PAID EMPLOYEES WHO COULD BE ^CULTIVATED^ AND COERCED INTO SUPPLYING INFO FOR MONEY. AGENTS WOULD PLAY ON THE EMOTIONS OF THESE LOW LEVEL VATICAN PERSONNEL WHO WERE ALREADY DISILLUSIONED WITH CATHOLICISM AND NO LONGER HELD ANY ALLEGIANCE TO THE CATHOLIC CHURCH. THE KGB ALSO REPORTEDLY TARGETED INTERPRETERS WORKING WITH HIGH-LEVEL OFFICES SUCH AS THE SECRETARIAT OF STATE AND THE COUNCIL OF PUBLIC AFFAIRS BECAUSE OF THEIR CLOSE PROXIMITY TO POLITICAL INFORMATION. THE REPORT NEVER ACTUALLY CONFIRMS THAT KGB WAS SUCCESSFUL IN INFILTRATING THE VATICAN~ HOWEVER~ ITALY HAS PUBLISHED A LIST OF INDIVIDUALS WHO WERE ON KGB'S PAYROLL. LIST~ COMPILED BY FORMER KGB ARCHIVIST VASILI MITROKHIN (WHO DEFECTED TO BRITAIN)~ INCLUDES THE HEAD OF THE OLD ITALIAN COMMUNIST PARTY~ ARMANDO COSSUTTA~ JOURNALISTS~ POLITICIANS AND OTHER INDIVIDUALS. BOTH COSSUTTA AND THE PRIME MINISTER~ MASSIMO D'ALEMA CLAIM LIST IS NOT AUTHENTIC. SOURCES ISSUE #78 10/13/99
